.TH WARRENVPNCTL 1 "2026" "WarrenVPN" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
warrenvpnctl \- command-line control for the WarrenVPN VPN daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B warrenvpnctl
.I command
[\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B warrenvpnctl
controls the WarrenVPN VPN daemon (\fBwarrenvpnd\fR) over D-Bus. It needs no GUI and is
suitable for headless or scripted use. With \fBWARRENVPN_BUS=session\fR it talks to a
daemon on the session bus (development).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List installed configurations with their current state and safe/unsafe status.
.TP
.B status
Show active connections and their state.
.TP
.B import \fIfile.ovpn\fR [\fIname\fR]
Import an OpenVPN configuration (the file is read locally and its contents sent to
the daemon, which classifies and stores a root-owned shadow copy).
.TP
.B connect \fIname|id\fR [\fB--killswitch\fR]
Start a connection and follow it, answering credential and static-challenge prompts
on the terminal. With \fB--killswitch\fR, block all non-tunnel egress while connected.
.TP
.B disconnect \fIname|id\fR
Disconnect a connection.
.TP
.B recover
Tear down the kill-switch and restore normal network connectivity.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error or a failed connection.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR warrenvpn (1),
.BR warrenvpnd (8),
.BR openvpn (8)
